---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: 'Snowpack - The faster frontend build tool'
description: 'Snowpack is the fast, bundle-free build tool for all kinds of frontend projects.'
---

<div class="home">
  <div class="grid-body-header">
    <div class="section">
      <h1 class="header-snowpack">Snowpack</h1>
      <p class="header-snowpack-subtitle">The faster frontend build tool.</p>

      <div class="header-cta">
        <a href="/getting-started" class="button">Get started</a>
        <div style="margin: 0.5rem"></div>
        <button  class="copy-button"  data-clipboard-text="npm install snowpack">
        <span  style="margin-right: 0.75rem;">$</span>
        npm install snowpack
        <svg style="height: 22px;width: 22px;margin: -0.1rem -0.1rem 0 0.75rem;" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" data-prefix="far" data-icon="clone" class="svg-inline--fa fa-clone fa-w-16" role="img" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 512 512"><path fill="currentColor" d="M464 0H144c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v48H48c-26.51 0-48 21.49-48 48v320c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h320c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48v-48h48c26.51 0 48-21.49 48-48V48c0-26.51-21.49-48-48-48zM362 464H54a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V150a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h42v224c0 26.51 21.49 48 48 48h224v42a6 6 0 0 1-6 6zm96-96H150a6 6 0 0 1-6-6V54a6 6 0 0 1 6-6h308a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v308a6 6 0 0 1-6 6z"></path></svg>
        </button>
        <script type="module">
          import Clipboard from 'https://cdn.skypack.dev/clipboard';
          const clippy = new Clipboard('.copy-button');
          clippy.on('success', function(e) {
              console.info('Trigger:', e.trigger.classList.add('active'));
              setTimeout(() => {e.trigger.classList.remove('active')}, 1000);
              e.clearSelection();
          });

        </script>
      </div>
      <div class="header-cta">
        <!-- Place this tag where you want the button to render. -->
        <div class="hidden-mobile" style="text-align: center">
          <a
            class="github-button"
            href="https://github.com/snowpackjs/snowpack"
            data-icon="octicon-star"
            data-size="large"
            data-show-count="true"
            aria-label="Star snowpackjs/snowpack on GitHub"
            >Star</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="container page-container">
    <aside
      class="grid-toc hidden-mobile"
      style="position: static; max-height: initial; z-index: auto"
    >
      {% include 'layouts/menu.njk' %}
    </aside>

    <article id="grid-body" class="grid-body">
      <a
        class="img-banner"
        href="https://osawards.com/javascript/2020"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        <img
          src="/img/JSAwardWinner.png"
          alt="2020 JavaScript Open Source Award Winner banner"
        />
      </a>

      <div class="content">
        <div class="home-grid">
          <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Fast</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Supports your code</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Deploy with ease</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>The Elevator Pitch</h2>
        <img src="/img/snowpack-unbundled-example-3.png" />
        <p>
          Every file is built individually and cached indefinitely. Your dev
          environment will never build a file more than once and your browser
          will never download a file twice (until it changes). This is the real
          power of unbundled development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

